    <h1 class="legal__title">Aftercare</h1>
    <p class="legal__lead">Your tattoo or piercing is fresh work. Treat it right and it will heal beautifully. Here is what we recommend.</p>

    <h2>Tattoo aftercare</h2>

    <h3>The first hours</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Keep the wrap or film on for the time your artist recommended — typically 2–4 hours for standard wrap, longer for second-skin film.</li>
      <li>Remove it gently with clean hands.</li>
      <li>Wash the tattoo carefully with unscented liquid soap and lukewarm water.</li>
      <li>Pat dry with a clean piece of kitchen towel — never a cloth.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>The first two weeks</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Apply a thin layer of unscented, alcohol-free moisturiser 2–3 times daily — Bepanthen, Lubriderm or similar.</li>
      <li>Keep the tattoo out of direct sunlight for at least 2–3 weeks.</li>
      <li>Avoid swimming pools, the sea, and baths — showers are fine.</li>
      <li>Do not scratch — even when it itches. It will itch.</li>
      <li>Do not pick at any peeling skin. Let it fall off on its own.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Healing</h3>
    <p>A tattoo is technically a wound. Surface healing takes 2–4 weeks. Full healing of the deeper layers can take up to 3 months. Peeling and mild flaking are completely normal during the first week.</p>

    <h3>When to contact us</h3>
    <p>Get in touch if you notice unusual redness, significant swelling, warmth, or discharge. These can be signs of infection. Call <a href="tel:{{ site.phoneIntl }}">{{ site.phone | replace(" ", "&nbsp;") | safe }}</a> or DM on <a href="{{ site.instagram }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Instagram</a>.</p>

    <h3>Sun and colour</h3>
    <p>Once fully healed, always apply SPF 50 sunscreen to your tattoo before sun exposure. UV light fades ink — especially colour and fineline.</p>

    <h2>Piercing aftercare</h2>

    <h3>Daily cleaning</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Clean twice daily with a sterile saline spray (0.9% NaCl) — NEILMED Wound Wash or similar.</li>
      <li>Only touch the piercing with thoroughly clean hands.</li>
      <li>Do not rotate or move the jewellery — this slows healing and increases infection risk.</li>
      <li>Pat dry gently after cleaning.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Healing times (approximate)</h3>
    <dl class="faq__hours">
      <div><dt>Earlobes</dt><dd>6–8 weeks</dd></div>
      <div><dt>Helix / tragus / conch</dt><dd>6–12 months</dd></div>
      <div><dt>Daith</dt><dd>6–12 months</dd></div>
      <div><dt>Nose</dt><dd>4–6 months</dd></div>
      <div><dt>Septum</dt><dd>6–8 weeks</dd></div>
      <div><dt>Navel</dt><dd>6–12 months</dd></div>
      <div><dt>Surface piercings</dt><dd>Individual — ask Emil</dd></div>
    </dl>

    <h3>What to avoid</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Changing the jewellery before the piercing is fully healed.</li>
      <li>Swimming pools, the sea, and hot tubs during the initial healing period.</li>
      <li>Makeup, perfume, and cleaning products directly on the piercing.</li>
      <li>Sleeping directly on a fresh ear piercing — use a travel pillow or a rolled-up pillow case.</li>
      <li>Touching the piercing unnecessarily.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Questions?</h3>
    <p>Emil is available in the shop or on Instagram. Do not hesitate to reach out if something looks off or you are unsure — better to ask early than wait.</p>

